revision.text:
{{pagebanner | Banner_-_Helsinki_5.jpg|pgname=Central Helsinki|caption=Detail of Helsinki Central railway station}}
'''Central Helsinki''' consists of the central parts of [[Helsinki]] east of [[Mannerheimintie]], south of Pitkäsilta, west of Unioninkatu and north of Esplanadi; in short the commercial downtown.
This is undoubtedly the liveliest part of Helsinki and much of what a visitor would like to see and experience is located in central Helsinki or — while in other districts — just a few hundred metres away. Here you can find the Central Railway Station with its surroundings; the art museums of Ateneum and Kiasma with the statue of Marshal Mannerheim in the front of the latter, modern architecture like the Oodi library, Sanomatalo and the Citycenter mall also known as the "Sausage house". One block south is Aleksanterinkatu, which together with its side streets make up Helsinki's main shopping area with small shops and department stores. And still one block south is Esplanadinpuisto, the Esplanade park that is very popular in the summer. The area also offers plenty of alternatives for eating and drinking, and some cultural venues.
==Get in== {{Mapframe|60.1720|24.9462|zoom=14}}
Getting in is easy as ''almost all'' local bus and rail lines end in or pass through the city centre, or at least enable you to get to central Helsinki with just one change, like the buses connecting to metro stations in the eastern suburbs. Moreover the {{marker|type=go|name=Helsinki Central Station|url=https://www.vr.fi/en/railway-stations-and-routes/helsinki|image=HelsinkiStationEntranceAndClockTower.jpg|lat=60.1711|long=24.9414}} is here, the bus station in [[Helsinki/Kamppi and Southwest|Kamppi]] about 500 m from the same and the passenger ports (except [[Vuosaari]]) are not far away.
If arriving by plane, you can get to the central railway station by the I or P trains going on the new Ring Rail Line, alternatively you can take bus 615 or a taxi.
==Get around==
Getting around the centre is probably easiest by foot or by bike. If you don't feel like walking, though, you can always use the metro or the trams provided you have a valid ticket.
==See== [[File:Esplanade park Helsinki.JPG|thumbnail|Esplanadinpuisto or just "Espa" is probably the best known park in Helsinki]] [[File:Helsinki Art Museum.JPG|thumb|Ateneum]]
* {{see | name=Esplanadi Park | alt=Esplanadinpuisto | url= | email= | address= | lat=60.167509 | long=24.947350 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Located between the market square (Kauppatori) and the two Esplanadi boulevards, this small but stately park has a commanding position at the heart of the city. In the summer time it is full of people sitting on the lawn, meeting their friends and quite often also having a drink or two. In the summer there are often free concerts given by local artists on the stage close to Kauppatori, facing restaurant Kappeli. If you're walking around with an ice cream or sandwich, do watch out for the aggressive birds. }} * {{see | name=Kaisaniemi Park | alt=Kaisaniemen puisto | url=http://www.luomus.fi/english/exhibitions/botanicgarden/index.htm | email= | address= | lat=60.174607 | long=24.944383 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2015-02-26 | content=In Kaisaniemi, north-east of the Central railway station. It has a bad reputation of a place where you might get assaulted, however in the daytime it's not more dangerous than any other place in Helsinki. The park has facilities for playing football (soccer) and tennis and is home to some events in the summer, most notably the morning of first of May and the festival "Maailma kylässä" in late May. It also holds Helsinki University's Botanical Garden (entrance from Kaisaniemenranta on the northern side). }} * {{see | name=Ateneum Art Museum | alt= | url=http://www.ateneum.fi | email= | address=Kaivokatu 2 | lat=60.170136 | long=24.944253 | directions= | phone=+358 9 173-361, +358 9 1733-6228 (for tickets) | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu–F 09:00–18:00, W Th 09:00–20:00, Sa Su 11:00–17:00, closed on Mondays | price=Adults €6, under 18 free, special prices may apply during major exhibitions. First Wednesday of the month 17:00–20:00 free admission |lastedit=2020-01-06 | content=Ateneum can be considered the most nationally significant art museum, and it has the largest collection of paintings and sculptures in Finland. Particularly notable is the collection of works by major Finnish artists. Works include renowned interpretations of the national epic Kalevala. }} * {{see | name=Kiasma Museum of Contemporary Art |alt=| url=http://www.kiasma.fi | email= | address=Mannerheiminaukio 2 | lat=60.17151 | long=24.93658 | directions= | phone=+358 9 1733-6501 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu 10:00–17:00, W–Su 10:00–20:30, closed on Mondays | price=€7 for adults, €5 for undergraduate students, senior citizens, visual artists, and groups with at least 7 people. Free admission for visitors under 18. First Friday of the month is free |lastedit=2020-01-06| content=The sometimes unusual collections mostly include works by contemporary Finnish artists and artists from nearby countries. There are also periodical exhibitions. The building is a work of art. }} * {{see | name=Paradox Museum Helsinki |alt=| url=https://paradoxmuseumhelsinki.com/en/ | email= | address=Fabianinkatu 29 | lat=60.16842 | long=24.94958 | directions=between Senate Square & Esplanade Park | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu–Th & Su 11:00–19.00, F–Sa 19:00–20:00, closed on Mondays | price=€23 for adults, €17 for children |lastedit=2025-03-29| content=An international museum for the whole family that plays with optical illusions, with over 40 different exhibitions. }} * {{see | name=Central Railway Station | alt=Päärautatieasema | url=https://paarautatieasema.fi/en | email= | address=Kaivokatu 1 / Vilhonkatu 13 | lat=60.1711 | long=24.9414 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2025-11-02 | content=The station building, clad in granite, was designed by Eliel Saarinen (the father of [[Eero Saarinen]]) and inaugurated in 1919. It has become the symbol of the entire railway network in Finland, and about 200,000 people pass through the station every day, half of whom are train passengers. Since 1 November 2025, there are guided tours to the clock tower (€24; stairs), with views over central Helsinki. The Olympia Stadium Tower is still much higher. }} * {{see | name=Main post office | alt=Postitalo/Pääposti/Huvudposten | url= | email= | address=Mannerheiminaukio 1 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikipedia= | wikidata=Q3399855 | lastedit=2019-11-11 | content=Across Mannerheimintie from Lasipalatsi is Helsinki's former main post office, designed by Jorma Järvi, Erik Lindroos and Kaarlo Borg and finished in 1938. However, it hasn't been the main post building since the late 1990s, but houses a number of shops, but the building is still protected as a valuable historical building (just like most buildings on this list). }} * {{see | name=Sanomatalo | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=60.1724 | long=24.9379 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | lastedit=2022-04-11 | content= }} * {{see | name=Equestrian statue of Marshal Mannerheim | alt= | url= | email= | address= |lat=60.17158 | long=24.93630 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | lastedit=2022-04-11 | content= }} * {{see | name=Metsätalo | alt= | url= | email= | address=Unioninkatu 40 | lat= | long= | directions=[[Helsinki/Central|Kaisaniemi]] | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikipedia= | wikidata=Q18660823 | lastedit=2019-11-11 | content=This university building has been described as having both functionalist and classicist elements. It was designed by Jussi Paatela, finished in 1939 and its first users were the State Forest Research Institute (Metsätutkimuslaitos) and Helsinki University's faculty for forest science, and that's where the building's name — "the forest house" — came from. Nowadays the building houses the linguistics and philology faculties. }} * {{see | name=Three Smiths Statue | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=60.168694 | long=24.941014 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2024-11-09 | content=A classic statue designed by the Finnish sculptor Felix Nylund, depicting three nude men hammering down on an anvil (except a study revealed that if the smiths were to actually hammer, they would hit each other on the head). A survey made by a Finnish newspaper resulted in this statue being the point most people think is the ''de facto'' centre point of the city of Helsinki. }}
==Do== From the {{Marker|type=do|lat=60.17077 | long=24.93901|name=restaurant on the top floor of the Sokos department store}} and the {{Marker|type=do|lat=60.16780 | long=24.93887 |name= bar on the top floor of Hotel Torni}} you have a quite nice '''view of the city'''. Of course they aren't as high as the Empire State Building or even the [[Helsinki/West#Olympic sights|Olympic Stadium Tower]] but entrance to both are free.
* {{do | name=Casino Helsinki | alt= | url=http://www.casinohelsinki.fi | email=asiakaspalvelu@ray.fi | address=Mikonkatu 19 | lat=60.17184 | long=24.94554 | directions= | phone=+358 9 680-800 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=12:00–04:00 | price= | content=Finland's only [[Gambling|gambling casino]]. It's next to the railway station. The only gambling casino in the world to donate 100% of its profits to charity. 2600 m² of floor space on two floors. About 300 slot machines and 20 gaming tables and several bars. Also includes a luxurious Show & Dinner restaurant, with prices ranging from €70 to €90 per person. }} * {{do | name=Kämp Spa | url=http://www.kampspa.fi/ | email=info@kampspa.fi | address=Kluuvikatu 4 B, (Kämp Gallery 8th floor) | lat=60.168722 | long=24.946665 | directions= | phone=+358 9 5761-1330 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–F 09:00–20:00, Su 09:00–13:00 and 16:00–20:00 (gym and sauna area) | price= | content=Kämp Spa is in the heart of Helsinki. In addition to the spa treatments, the spa has a gym and 3 different saunas. }} [[File:Auditorium at Maxim in May 2024.jpg|thumb|right|All the seats at Maxim are large and plush armchairs.]] * {{do | name=Maxim | alt= | url=https://www.finnkino.fi/teatterit/maxim | email= | address=Kluuvikatu 1 | lat=60.168186 | long=24.947906 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2024-05-31 | content=The oldest film theatre in Finland. It is owned by Finnkino, carrying the more artistic side of Finnkino's programme. Only two auditoriums, and no 3D or IMAX technology, but this is still a unique experience. All the seats in both auditoriums are large and plush armchairs with plenty of leg room. The bar at the theatre is well stocked with tapas-style food and both alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks, and you can take all of it with you to the film. }} * {{do | name=Helsinki Central Library Oodi | alt= | url= | email= | address= | lat=60.1736 | long=24.9381 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | lastedit=2022-04-11 | content= }} * {{do | name=Outdoor Icepark skating | alt= | url=http://icepark.fi | email= | address=Railway Station Square | lat=60.171136 | long=24.943465 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=In winter | price= | content=A pair of skates can be rented for an additional fee. The connected café offers the opportunity of defrosting with a cup of hot glögi. There are also dozens of other places to go skating in Helsinki, including [https://www.hel.fi/helsinki/en/culture/sports/outdoor/artificial-and-skating-rinks/ outdoor] and [https://www.hel.fi/helsinki/en/culture/sports/indoor/skating/ indoor] skating rinks. }}
===Theatre=== Performances are mostly either in Finnish or Swedish. The [[Helsinki/Inner East#Tokoinranta|city theatre]] (Kaupunginteatteri, Finnish) is in Kallio to the north, across Eläintarhanlahti.
* {{do | name=National Theatre | alt=Kansallisteatteri | url=http://www.kansallisteatteri.fi/briefly-in-english/ | email= | address=Läntinen Teatterikuja 1 | lat=60.17214 | long=24.94394 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content= }} * {{do | name=Swedish Theatre | alt=Svenska Teatern | url=http://www.svenskateatern.fi | email= | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 2 | lat=60.16736 | long=24.94360 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content= }}
==Buy== ===Department stores and shopping malls=== [[File:2009-09-19-helsinki-by-RalfR-114.jpg|thumbnail|Shopping in Stockmann]]
Helsinki's main shopping drag is '''Aleksanterinkatu''' (''Aleksi''), which runs from the Senate Square (Senaatintori) to Mannerheimintie. On Aleksi you can find plenty of shops and the largest department store in Scandinavia, Stockmann, which is definitely worth a visit. The parallel '''Esplanadi''' boulevards have specialist and generally very expensive boutiques. Access to the area is easy, as trams 2, 4 and 7 all run down Aleksanterinkatu, and the area is near the Central Railway Station and Kaisaniemi metro stations. Close by, in the Kamppi area, you can find the shopping centres Kamppi and Forum and the department store Sokos. Large shopping malls can be found in the suburbs and accessed by public transport from the Central Railway Station.
* {{buy | name=Akateeminen Kirjakauppa | alt=Akademiska bokhandeln | url=http://www.akateeminen.com | email= | address=Keskuskatu (''opposite Stockmann'') | lat= 60.16786 | long= 24.94343 | directions=Tram: 2, 4, 6, 7, 9, 10. | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=The largest bookstore in Northern Europe, with extensive selections in English too. An underground passage connects the bookstore to Stockmann. If for no other reason the bookstore's architecture (Alvar Aalto) and pleasant second floor cafeteria (one of the few with to-table service in Helsinki) might be enough reason to visit. }} * {{buy | name=Stockmann | alt= | url=http://www.stockmann.fi/portal/en | email= | address=Corner of Aleksanterinkatu and Mannerheimintie | lat= 60.16841 | long= 24.94173 | directions=Tram: 2, 4, 6, 7, 9, 10. | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | wikidata=Q644390 | content=Northern Europe's largest department store. The flagship of Finland's premier department store chain. When Helsinkians meet "under the clock" (''kellon alla''), they mean the one rotating under the main entrance to Stockmann. Large selection of souvenirs and Finnish goods, and the Herkku supermarket in the basement offers an amazing range of gourmet food from all over Europe. There are also smaller branches of Stockmann at the malls of Itäkeskus, Jumbo, Tapiola and the airport. }} * {{buy | name=Galleria Esplanad | alt= | url=http://www.galleriaesplanad.fi | email= | address=between Mikonkatu and Kluuvikatu | lat=60.16843 | long=24.94661 | directions=Tram: 2, 4, 6, 7, 9. Metro: Kaisaniemi | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | content=Upscale shopping mall, with local brands like Marimekko, Aarikka and Iittala. }} * {{buy | name=Kluuvi | alt= | url=http://kluuvi.fi/?q=english&set=true#home | email= | address=Aleksanterinkatu | lat= 60.16933 | long= 24.94828 | directions=Tram: 2, 4, 7. Metro: Kaisaniemi. | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Re-opened after extensive renovations in 2011, the Kluuvi shopping centre features a range of international and domestic brands. Perhaps the most interesting concept is the Eat & Joy Markethall selling organic and local food in the basement. Grind your own flour and fill your bottles with crude milk but be prepared for steep prices. }} * {{buy | name=Sokos | alt= | url=https://www.sokos.fi/fi/sokos/myymalat/sokos-helsinki | email= | address=Mannerheimintie 9 | lat= 60.17052 | long= 24.93862 | directions=Tram: 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 9, 10, Metro: Central Railway Station. | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A large department store next to the railway station. Good place for buying clothes, you can often find the same products here as in nearby Stockmann but at a lower price. On the downside, despite being a department store they have a rather limited selection of everything else. The restaurant at the top floor has a nice view of central Helsinki. }} * {{buy | name=Citycenter | alt= | url=https://citycenter.fi/en/ | email= | address= | lat=60.1696 | long=24.9414 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | lastedit=2022-04-11 | content= }}
===Design=== * {{buy | name=Iittala Shop | alt= | url=http://www.iittala.fi | email= | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 25 | lat= 60.16796 | long= 24.94920 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–F 10:00–19:00, Sa 10:00–16:00 | price= | content=An airy concept store for the Iittala brand of Finnish glassware, pans, kitchen utensils and more. Personal service by the friendly staff. }} * {{buy | name=Left Shoe Company | alt= | url=http://www.leftshoecompany.com/ | email= | address=Eteläesplanadi 8B (also inside Stockmann department store) | lat=60.1671 | long=24.94933 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | content=Step on a high tech gadget that measures your foot and then choose what sort of shoe you would like to wear. Get the tailored shoe sent home by post. Only men's shoes. Prices start at around €300 and go up €450 depending on the materials used. }} * {{buy | name=Marimekko | alt= | url=http://www.marimekko.com | email= | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 33 | lat= 60.16786 | long= 24.94600 | directions= | phone=+358 9 686-0240 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Innovative and unique Finnish interior design, bags, and fabrics. This is the flagship store, but items can also be found at the Kämp Gallery, Kamppi Centre, Hakaniemi Market Hall, or their factory shop. }} ** {{buy | name=factory shop | alt= | url= | email= | address=Kirvesmiehenkatu 7 | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+358 9 758-7244 | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikipedia= | wikidata= | lastedit= | content= }} * {{buy | name=Eat and Joy Farmers Market | alt= | url= | email= | address=Aleksanterinkatu 7–9 | lat= 60.16910 | long= 24.94820 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=In the heart of Helsinki at Kluuvi shopping centre, another one at Helsinki Airport. The markets are open seven days a week and have delicacies from more than 500 small producers across Finland: wild reindeer (poro), salmon, artisan cheeses, berry jams, fish roe, hand-crafted beer and cider, mushrooms, rye bread, smoked specialities, kyyttö forest cow, artisan chocolates and many other products – all direct from the producers. }}
==Eat== ===Budget=== [[File:Fast food grill at Rautatientori in Helsinki, Finland, 2023 March.jpg|thumb|A grill kiosk at the Railway Square]] * {{eat | name=Chilli | alt=Mikonkatu 8 | url= | email= | address= | lat=60.16966 | long=24.94246 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | lastedit=2022-08-01 | content=Cheap kebab, shawarma, and falafel. Large portions, though be warned that this isn't your traditional Middle Eastern fare. Pitas come with something akin to spaghetti sauce inside. Filling choice, especially on a budget. }} * {{eat | name=Pronto Central Station | alt= | url=https://oliviarestaurants.fi/ravintola/pronto/ | email= | address=Kaivokatu 1 | lat=60.170778 | long=24.941248 | directions= | phone=+358 50 3844800 | tollfree= | hours=08:00 to 19:00 mostly | price=About 8 € | lastedit=2024-11-02 | content=A little, cosy Italian-style restaurant and café located at the Helsinki Central railway station. Pronto is the "little sister" of the larger restaurant Olivia located right next to it. Serves pizza al taglio, focaccia and Italian-style coffee. Not to be confused with restaurant Pronto Pizzeria in Sörnäinen. }} * {{eat | name=Pystygrilli | url= | email= | address=Rautatientori | lat=60.1710 | long=24.9447 | directions=the Railway Square | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Daily 20:00–05:00 | price=€5–10 | lastedit=2024-06-23 | content=The 12-square-meter grill kiosk since 1940. }} * {{eat | name=Sodexo | url=http://www.sodexo.fi | email= | address=Multiple places | lat= | long= | directions= | phone=+358 41 783-9069 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M-F 08:00–15:00, lunch: 10:30–13:30 | price=Around €9.60 for lunch. | lastedit= | content= }} * {{eat | name=Unicafe Ylioppilasaukio | alt= | url=http://www.unicafe.fi/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=47&Itemid=46&kampusid=1 | email= | address=Mannerheimintie 3 B | lat=60.16897 | long=24.94064 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Open M–F 11:00–19:00, Sa 11:00–17:00 | price= | lastedit= | content=The biggest and most centrally located student restaurant and cafeteria is only a two-minute walk away from the main railway station. The standard lunch price (including drink, bread and salad buffet) is €8, there is also a "light" option (soup and salad) for €7 and "special" course for €9.50. Discounts apply if you happen to own a Finnish student card. }} * {{eat | name=Shoku Burger | alt= | url=https://www.shokuburger.com | email=shokuburger@shokuburger.com | address=Vuorikatu 14 | lat=60.17173 | long=24.94695 | directions=next to Helsinki University (former Kaisaniemi) metro station | phone=+358 50-551-1316 | tollfree= | hours= | price= | wikidata= | lastedit=2025-04-10 | content=An "Asian burger" place, formerly operating in Mikkola, north-eastern Vantaa. They make delicious burgers with East Asian flavour. }}
===Mid-range=== [[File:Tractor driver's steak at restaurant Zetor.jpg|thumb|right|"Tractor driver's steak" is one of Zetor's most famous dishes]]
====Finnish==== * {{eat | name=Bastard Burgers| alt= | url=https://bastardburgers.com/fi/restaurants/mikonkatu/ | email=mikonkatu@bastardburgers.fi | address=Mikonkatu 6 | lat=60.16935 | long=24.94537 | directions= | phone=+358 40-164-6494 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–Th 10:30–22:00, F Sa 10:30–01:00, Su 12:00–21:00 | price= | lastedit=2023-06-18 | content=A hamburger restaurant, where burgers are served with beef produced only on Finnish farms. }} * {{eat | name=Zetor | alt= | url=http://www.zetor.net/ | email= | address=Kaivopiha, Mannerheimintie 3–5 | lat=60.16943 | long=24.94074 | directions= | phone=+358 9 666-966 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Main meals €10–20. | content=Tourist restaurant with lots of character and great quality Finnish food. Plenty of old tractors and Finnish memorabilia. At night time Zetor functions as a popular and trendy night club with various funky music both from Finland and abroad, with plenty of young people attending. The kitchen stays open until closing time. Note that at night time, there tend to be long queues to get into Zetor in the first place. }}
====International==== [[File:Pizza Phangan Lover.jpg|thumb|right|Pizza "Phangan Lover" with crayfish, red onion, jalapeños, chili mayonnaise and fresh tomato]]
Central Helsinki is dominated by restaurants dedicated to international cuisine, and these are particularly useful for vegetarian visitors, Finnish food being largely meat-based. A particular touch is provided by a bunch of "Nepalese" restaurants, which actually serve generic north Indian food, but almost any of which you are guaranteed to leave happy and full. Localized Chinese and Italian cuisines are also well represented.
In 2020 the former Suomalainen Kirjakauppa bookstore, below the old student house, next to the three smith's square (Kolmen sepän aukio, across Aleksanterinkatu from Stockmann) was turned into a kind of foodcourt with a lot of restaurants and bars plus some shops. It's a wing of the [https://www.kaivopiha.fi/#top Kaivopiha] shopping complex.
* {{eat | name=Amarillo | alt= | url=https://www.raflaamo.fi/fi/ravintola/helsinki/amarillo-helsinki | email= | address=Aleksanterinkatu 46 | lat=60.168814 | long=24.945226 | directions= | phone=+358 10 7664680 | tollfree= | hours=15:00 to 21:00 mostly | price=Main courses 20 € to 40 € | lastedit=2024-10-06 | content=Tex-Mex cuisine for Finnish tastes. Steaks, burritos, fajitas, burgers and salads. All food is very tasty but don't expect completely authentic Mexican cuisine. }} * {{eat | name=Bangkok 9 | alt= | url=https://www.bangkok9restaurant.com | email= | address=Kaivokatu 8 | lat=60.169716 | long=24.940505 | directions= | phone=+358 50-463-3833 | tollfree= | hours=12:00–20:00 mostly | price=Main courses €16 to 20 | lastedit=2019-03-10 | content=A Thai cuisine restaurant in the City-Center complex in central Helsinki, opposite the central railway station. Offers authentic spicy Thai cuisine. Interesting decor. Usually a bit crowded. }} * {{eat | name=Belge | alt= | url=https://www.raflaamo.fi/fi/helsinki/belge | email= | address=Kluuvikatu 5 (''Kauppakeskus Kluuvi'') | lat=60.16930 | long=24.94768 | directions= | phone=+358 9 622-9620 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Main dishes €12–17 | content=A reasonable selection of Belgian beers, a nice range of bistro fare, and a good location for people watching. The dining room upstairs is non-smoking. The menus in the dining rooms are served inside Tintin comic books in Finnish, so you can read them while deciding what to order. }} * {{eat | name=Brasserie Kämp | alt= | url=https://www.brasseriekamp.fi/?lang=en | email=kamp_cafe@hotelkamp.fi | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 29 | lat=60.16790 | long=24.94719 | directions= | phone=+358 9 5840-9530 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–W 11:30–00:00, Th F 11:30–01:00, Sa 12:00–01:00, Su 12:00–00:00 | price= | content= }} * {{eat | name=China Tiger | alt= | url=http://www.dongbeihu.fi/ {{dead link|December 2020}} | email=hu@dongbeihu.fi | address=Korkeavuorenkatu 47 | lat=60.16686 | long=24.94604 | directions= | phone=+358 9 949-5098 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–F 11:00–23:00, Sa Su 12:00–23:00 | price=Lunch €9.2, mains from €12.8 | content=One of the best Chinese restaurants in Helsinki. Excellent food, a nice atmosphere and really good service. Extra points for the interior design. }} * {{eat | name=Classic Pizza | alt= | url=http://www.classicpizza.fi | email= | address=Aleksanterinkatu 52 | lat=60.16835 | long=24.94218 | directions= | phone=+358 9 121-3838 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=€14–17 | lastedit=2015-12-20 | content=A classy, fashionable pizzeria with a wide variety of pizzas on the menu. Some of the toppings might be rather unusual, such as grilled chicken, pickled cucumbers, beetroot, crayfish, bratwurst, coconut milk, or Finnish ''leipäjuusto'' cheese. But the end result is a tasty culinary treat anyway. For dessert, there's a pizza with ice cream and fresh fruit.<br/>The restaurant has several locations around the Helsinki capital area and elsewhere in Finland, but the most central one is in the Stockmann department store, on the basement floor.<br/>The restaurant is rather self-consciously a pizzeria. Although many other pizzerias in Helsinki also serve kebab, there are only pizzas on the menu here, and even the staff wear shirts saying "Sorry, no kebab". }} * {{eat | name=La Famiglia | alt= | url=https://www.raflaamo.fi/fi/ravintola/helsinki/la-famiglia-helsinki | email= | address=Keskuskatu 3 | lat= 60.16904 | long=24.94264 | directions= | phone=+358 9 8568-5680 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= daily 11:00–00:00| price= | lastedit= | content=Unpretentious Italian food even for under €20. The weekday lunch buffet of soup, salad and two kinds of pasta (€13.50) is still a particularly good value. }} * {{eat | name=Meze Point | alt= | url= | email= | address=Mikonkatu 8 | lat= 60.16959 | long= 24.94521 | directions= | phone=+358 9 622-2625 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Main dishes €15–20 | content=Mediterranean meze plates, several vegetarian dishes. Excellent vegetarian moussaka. }} * {{eat | name=Tawook Lab | alt= | url=https://linktr.ee/TawookLab?utm_source=linktree_profile_share&ltsid=10804d3b-e9f1-4e1b-8dcb-5539ade7eceb | email= | address=Citykäytävä, Aleksanterinkatu 21 | lat= 60.1689 | long= 24.9414 | directions=at Citycenter | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–Th 11:00–21:00, F 11:00–22:00, Sa 12:00–22:00, Su 12:00–19:00 | price=€15–20 | content=A Syrian restaurant. }} * {{eat | name=Woolshed | alt= | url=https://woolshed.eu/ | email=helsinki@woolshed.eu | address=Töölönlahdenkatu 3B | lat=60.173396 | long=24.939097 | directions= | phone=+358 44 760 4086 | tollfree= | hours=11:00 to 24:00 mostly | price=Main courses €17-30 | lastedit=2024-08-02 | content=A distinctly Australian gastropub and restaurant right in the centre of Helsinki, in an office building right next to the Helsinki Central railway station. The menu is rather meat-oriented. A wide selection of Australian and international beers and wines available. Serves affordable lunch on weekdays. Note that the staff don't speak any Finnish, only English. }}
===Splurge=== [[File:Restaurant Kappeli in March.jpg|thumb|right|Restaurant Kappeli stands prominently out in the middle of the Esplanadi park]] [[File:Vltava on Elielinaukio in Kluuvi, Helsinki, Finland, 2022 June.jpg|thumb|Restaurant Vltava at Elielinaukio]]
* {{eat | name=Caverna | alt= | url=https://www.caverna.fi | email=info@caverna.fi | address=Yliopistonkatu 5 | lat=60.169884 | long=24.947100 | directions= | phone=+ 358 50-555-9325 | tollfree= | hours=11:00–21:00 mostly | price=Buffet €39 | lastedit=2020-01-19 | content=A large restaurant located in the basement, offering a diverse buffet mainly concentrating on Spanish cuisine. Various kinds of appetisers, main courses and desserts on offer, all for a fixed price of €39 (alcoholic drinks cost extra). For the main course, you select the meats when they are still raw, the restaurant cooks them for you and brings them to your table. }} * {{eat | name=Harald | alt= | url=http://www.ravintolaharald.fi | email=helsinki@ravintolaharald.fi | address=Aleksanterinkatu 21 | lat=60.16890 | long=24.94161 | directions= | phone=+358 44-766-8010 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=11:00–22:00 mostly | price=Main courses €18–35 | lastedit=2016-06-16 | content=A Viking-themed restaurant that tries to keep its cuisine as close to the authentic Viking cuisine as possible, but still keeping in with today's tastes. In practice, the food is extremely tasty, but a bit overpriced. The decor is Viking-themed, the staff dress up in Viking-themed costumes, and even the menu contains Viking-era descriptions. The menu is obviously very meat-oriented, but there are some vegetarian options available. Try the duck or beef dishes, they're very tasty. The restaurant servers its own beer, it's worth trying. }} * {{eat | name=Kappeli | alt= | url=http://www.kappeli.fi/english_chapel.html | email= | address=Eteläesplanadi 1 | lat= 60.16744 | long= 24.95058 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Main lunch dishes €14–18, main dinner dishes about €15–36 | content=Traditional Finnish dishes: reindeer, fish, etc. Some of the prices are a bit high, but you should get polite service and well-prepared food with a lovely presentation. Cosy, relaxed, relatively quiet atmosphere (although the restaurant is apparently well-known and therefore might be more crowded during late evenings & tourist season). The roasted lamb with garlic potatoes is a good choice, as is their take on Finnish-style blueberry pie. They also offer a cheaper self-service café on the left side of the restaurant, along with a bar (opened in 1867) in the middle of the building. }} * {{eat | name=Papa Andreas | alt= | url= https://www.papaandreas.fi/ | email=opa@papaandreas.fi | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 37 | lat=60.16806 | long=24.94416 | directions= | phone=+358 40 551 0444 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–Th 11:00–23:00, F 11:00–00:00, Sa 12:00–00:00, Su 12:00–21:00 | price=€50 | content=A Greek restaurant. }} * {{eat | name=Savoy | alt= | url= http://www.royalravintolat.com/savoy/en/index.asp| email= | address=Eteläesplanadi 14 | lat=60.16705 | long=24.94713 | directions= | phone=+358 9 684-4020 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A luxurious restaurant with a magnificent view of downtown Helsinki's rooftops. Savoy is decorated just as Alvar Aalto designed it in the 1930s, and they still serve some of the dishes that Field Marshal Mannerheim used to order, such as the famous ''Vorschmack'' (a comparatively cheap €18). Other mains from €40, while the opulent "Menu Savoy" will set you back €102. }} * {{eat | name=Vltava | alt= | url=https://vltava.fi | email=ravintolavltava@sok.fi | address=Elielinaukio 2 | lat=60.17143 | long=24.93967 | directions=by the railway station | phone=+358 10-766-3650 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=11:00–23:00 mostly | price=Main courses €20–32 | wikidata=Q11901817 | image=Vltava (restaurant), 2019 (01).jpg | lastedit=2025-05-11 | content=The best Czech restaurant in Helsinki. Several floors on the premises, the ground floor consisting of a bar, the upper ones of a restaurant. Several Czech beers on tap, and the menu is based on Czech cuisine with copious amounts of sausages and sauerkraut. }}
==Drink== ===Cafes=== [[File:Esplanaden in Helsinki 01.jpg|thumbnail|The Esplanade offers some nice upscale cafés]]
* {{drink | name=Café Höijer | alt= | url=https://en.ateneumbistro.fi | email= | address=Kaivokatu 20 | lat=60.170136 | long=24.944253 | directions=at the Ateneum Art Museum; on third floor | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=Tu–F 12:00–19:00, weekend 12:00–17:00 | price= | content= }} * {{drink | name=Café Kafka | alt= | url= | email= | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 2 | lat=60.16756 | long= 24.94360 | directions=Swedish Theatre | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A lovely building with a relaxed atmosphere. Here you can find one of the best espressos in town. }} * {{drink | name=Fazer | alt= | url= | email= | address=Kluuvikatu 3 | lat=60.16854 | long= 24.94773 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Famous for its decor, architecture, ice-creams, pastries and coffees, this café opened in 1891, run by Finland's largest chocolate maker, has been an institution since its birth. There's also the Fazer Bakery shop next to the café. If you are visiting, pay attention to the round room topped with a dome. People say that if you tell secrets here, the other customers will hear them across the room due to the acoustics of the dome. }} * {{drink | name=Kämp Café | alt= | url=https://www.brasseriekamp.fi/?lang=en | email=kamp_cafe@hotelkamp.fi | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 29 | lat=60.16789 | long=24.94731 | directions= | phone=+358 9 5840-9530 | tollfree= | fax= | hours=M–W 11:30–00:00, Th F 11:30–01:00, Sa 12:00–01:00, Su 12:00–00:00 | price= | content= }} * {{drink | name=Strindberg | alt= | url=https://www.strindberg.fi/en/home/ | email=myynti@noho.fi | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 33 | lat=60.1679 | long=24.9462 | directions=at Schoffa; near the Esplanadi Park and Hotel Kämp | phone=+358 9 6128-6900 | tollfree= | hours=Restaurant: M–F 11:30–23:00, Sa 13:00–23:00; café: M–Th 09:00–20:00, F 09:00–21:00, Sa 10:00–21:00, Su 12:00–19:00 | price=Lunch €12–29; main courses €24–38; café €15–18 | lastedit=2024-03-09 | content=One of the oldest and most historic cafés of Helsinki. Great terrace on the posh Pohjoisesplanadi with views of the Esplanadi park, restaurant on the 2nd floor. Also high-quality pastries and modern Nordic food and drink. Very popular among locals. }}
===Bars and pubs=== * {{drink | name=Butterfly | alt=previously '''Baarikärpänen''' | url= | email= | address= | lat= 60.17111 | long=24.94547 | directions=in Mikonkatu, next to the Central Railway Station | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Offers R & B and Top 40 hits in a nice lounge-type bar with big comfortable sofas and a dance floor. Reasonably cheap. }} * {{drink | name=Molly Malone's | alt= | url=http://mollymalones.fi | email= | address=Kaisaniemenkatu 1 | lat=60.17090 | long=24.94640 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=An Irish pub/nightclub near the Central Railway Station. Popular among Finns and tourists alike. Live music every night, superb English-language cover bands most nights, sometimes a DJ later. If you happen to be in Helsinki at St.Patrick's Day (March 17th) this is definitely where you should go. Avoid the blackjack table unless you're fond of losing money (the proceeds do go to charity). }} * {{drink | name=On The Rocks | alt= | url=http://www.ontherocks.fi | email= | address=Mikonkatu 15 | lat= 60.17093 | long=24.94550 | directions=near Central Railway Station | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=Located next to Baarikärpänen and Texas, this is a rock-oriented bar with occasional live bands and stand up comedy acts. Minimum age 18. }} * {{drink | name=Pikajuna Ale bar | url= | email= | address= | lat= | long= | directions= next to the Central Railway Station, close to Casino Helsinki | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A bar with beer from €3.9. Features games like billiards and board games. Spacious. }} * {{drink | name=Thirsty Scholar | alt= | url=https://www.thirstyscholar.fi/en/frontpage/ | email=pub@thirstyscholar.fi | address=Fabianinkatu 37 | lat=60.171513 | long=24.949261 | directions= | phone=+358 44-988-2132 | tollfree= | hours=M–Sa 15:00–00:00, closed Su | price= | lastedit=2023-09-04 | content=A pub with a spacious inner courtyard terrace in central Helsinki. Several beers and ciders available on tap and in bottles. University students get a discount on drinks on tap. }} * {{drink | name=Vanha ylioppilastalo | alt=usually just '''Vanha''' | url=http://www.vanhaylioppilastalo.fi/fi/tapahtumat/ | email= | address=Mannerheimintie 3 | lat=60.16909 | long=24.94074 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A bar/café opposite Stockmann, owned by University of Helsinki's filthy rich students' union. Not very special in the winter, but the rooftop patio in the summer is nice. In the evenings, the club attracts a slightly-over-18 audience. }}
===Nightclubs=== [[File:Mummotunneli.jpg|thumb|right|The entrance to Mummotunneli in June.]]
* {{drink | name=Mummotunneli | alt= | url= | email= | address=Aleksanterinkatu 46 | lat=60.16842 | long=24.94509 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours=20:00–03:00 | price=€10 entry fee | lastedit=2015-12-06 | content=The "Mummotunneli" ("Grandma tunnel") is a passage between various restaurants in central Helsinki. There are terraces of various restaurants in the passage, staying open well past midnight. The name "Grandma tunnel" comes from the alleged high average age of the clients. In practice, this means you will usually meet people from 30 to 50 years. Very few actual grandmas come here. Live music available pretty much every day. The place is extremely crowded in summer but almost deserted in winter. }} * {{drink | name=Teatteri | alt= | url=http://www.teatteri.fi | email= | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 2 | lat= 60.16759 | long= 24.94410 | directions= | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | content=A complex featuring a deli, a restaurant, a bar and a night club, all of them trendy and popular among the well-dressed crowd. Check out the aptly named Clock Bar (''Kellobaari'') downstairs. Closed Sunday. }} * {{drink | name=Hercules Gay Night Club | alt= | url=http://www.herculesgayclub.com | email=herculesgayclub@gmail.com | address=Keskuskatu 8 B (3rd floor) | lat=60.17007 | long=24.94201 | directions=at Kauppakeskus Citycenter | phone= | tollfree= | hours= | price= | content=One of the busiest gay nightclubs in Scandinavia, mainly a 30+ clients, dance floor and 2 bare, good for bare-faced cruising. Entrance free; coat check €2.50 (on special guests nights fees may vary). }}
==Sleep== [[File:Hotel Kämp.JPG|thumbnail|Hotel Kämp, Helsinki's own "Hôtel Ritz"]]
===Budget=== As with other major cities, if you're looking for low-cost accommodation it's better to head a bit outside the very core of the city.
===Mid-range=== * {{sleep | name=Best Western Hotel Carlton | url=http://www.bestwestern.fi/etsi_hotelli/hotel_carlton.213.xhtml {{dead link|December 2020}} | email=carlton.booking@carlton.fi | address=Kaisaniemenkatu 3 | lat= 60.17097 | long= 24.94693 | directions=100 m from the railway station | phone=+358 9 684-1320 | tollfree= | fax=+358 9 660-112 | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=19-room hotel. }} * {{sleep | name=Cumulus Kaisaniemi | url=http://www.cumulus.fi/hotellit/kaisaniemi/en_GB/kaisaniemi/ | email= | address=Kaisaniemenkatu 7 | lat= 60.17168 | long= 24.94785 | directions=M Kaisaniemi | phone= | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=From €83 off season | checkin= | checkout= | content=Minimally equipped business hotel. }} * {{sleep | name=Hobo Hotel| url=https://hobohotel.fi | email=stay@hobohotel.fi | address=Kluuvikatu 4 | lat=60.16855 | long=24.94714 | directions=between Aleksanterinkatu and Pohjoisesplanadi, next door to Kämp | phone=+358 10-344-4400 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price= | checkin= | checkout= | content=Formerly GLO Helsinki. }} * {{sleep | name=Hotel Arthur | alt= | url=https://www.hotelarthur.fi/en/ | email=reception@hotelarthur.fi | address=Vuorikatu 19 | lat=60.17298 | long=24.94842 | directions=200 meters from Central Railway Station | phone=+358 9 173-441 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2023-09-01 | content= }}
===Splurge=== * {{sleep | name=Hotel Kämp | url=https://www.hotelkamp.com/en | email=sales@hotelkamp.com | address=Pohjoisesplanadi 29 | lat=60.16790 | long=24.94723 | directions= | phone=+358 9 576-111 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=Rooms from €120 | checkin= | checkout= | content=Opened 1887, this historic hotel claims to be the only true 5-star in Scandinavia, with doormen in top hats, yacht charters and prices to match: the eight-room Mannerheim Suite can be yours for only €3300 per night. }} * {{sleep | name=Grand Hansa | url=https://www.nh-collection.com/en/hotel/nh-collection-helsinki-grand-hansa | email=nhcollectionhelsinki@nh-hotels.com | address=Mannerheimintie 5 | lat=60.16936 | long=24.93997 | directions= | phone=+358 20-712-0290 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=From €170 | checkin=15:00 | checkout=12:00 | content=A 5-star hotel in the city centre including over 200 spacious and luxurious rooms and suites of various sizes. }} * {{sleep | name=Radisson Blu Plaza | url=http://www.radissonblu.com/plazahotel-helsinki | email=info.plaza.helsinki@radissonblu.com | address=Mikonkatu 23 | lat=60.17258 | long=24.94538 | directions= | phone=+358 20-123-4700 | tollfree= | fax= | hours= | price=From €150 | checkin= | checkout= | content=Classy hotel in a protected and carefully renovated, Kalevala-inspired 1917 building. Excellent breakfast buffet. }} * {{sleep | name=Sokos Hotel Helsinki | alt= | url=https://www.sokoshotels.fi/fi/helsinki/sokos-hotel-helsinki/ | email=hotelhelsinki.helsinki@sokoshotels.fi | address=Kluuvikatu 8 |lat=60.16962 | long=24.94718| directions= | phone=+358 20-1234-601 | tollfree= | fax=+358 9 176-014 | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2015-09-16 | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Sokos Hotel Vaakuna | alt= | url=https://www.sokoshotels.fi/fi/helsinki/sokos-hotel-vaakuna/ | email=vaakuna.helsinki@sokoshotels.fi | address=Asema-Aukio 2 | lat=60.17056 | long=24.93883 | directions= | phone=+358 20-123-4610 | tollfree= | fax=+358 9 4337 7100 | checkin= | checkout= | price= | lastedit=2015-09-16 | content= }} * {{sleep | name=Holiday Inn Helsinki City Centre | alt= | url=http://www.ihg.com/holidayinn/hotels/us/en/helsinki/helek/hoteldetail | email=hihcc@holidayinnhelsinki.fi | address=Elielinaukio 5 | lat=60.17251 | long=24.93947 | directions= | phone=+358 9 5245-5000 | tollfree= | fax= | checkin=15:00 | checkout=12:00 | price= | lastedit=2024-05-21 | content= }}
==Connect== Cafés and shopping centres usually have a Wi-Fi of some sort (the speed might not be the best on the markets). The central train station has good Wi-Fi coverage and at decent speed.
While the city advertises its Wi-Fi, the access points are clustered at certain locations and do not provide widespread coverage (for example, none on the busy thoroughfare Mannerheimintie south of the Central Train Station).
==Respect== If you are into flying drones, quadcopters or other unmanned aircraft, please note that there is a "no-drone-zone" over the historic city centre. There is more information at, [https://www.droneinfo.fi/en droneinfo.fi].
